<section xml:id="sec-4-1-what-we-assume-ch-04" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Our Assumptions</title>
    <p>In this chapter you can assume anything you had in <xref ref="sec-4-1-1-what-we-assume"/>. We also include a few more definitions for this chapter.</p>
    <p></p>


    <p>
        <definition xml:id="defn-divisor">
            <title>Common Divisor</title>
            <idx><h>common divisor</h></idx>
            <statement>
            <p>
                <m>\forall a,b,c\in\Z</m>, all non-zero, we call <m>c</m> a <term>common divisor</term>
                of <m>a</m> and <m>b</m> iff <m>c</m> divides <m>a</m> and <m>c</m> divides <m>b</m>.
            </p>
            </statement>
        </definition>
    </p>
    <p>
        <definition xml:id="defn-gcd">
            <title>Greatest Common Divisor</title>
            <idx><h>greatest common divisor</h></idx>
            <statement>
            <p>
                <m>\forall a,b,c\in\Z</m>, all non-zero, we call <m>c</m> the <term>greatest common divisor</term>
                of <m>a</m> and <m>b</m>, denoted <m>c=\text{GCD}(a,b)</m> iff 
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>c</m> is a common divisor of <m>a</m> and <m>b</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            every common divisor of <m>d\in\Z</m> of <m>a</m> and <m>b</m> has 
                            the property <m>d\leq c</m>. (every other divisor is smaller)
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
            </statement>
        </definition>
    </p>
    <p>
        <definition xml:id="defn-rational">
            <title>Rational</title>
            <idx><h>rational number</h></idx>
            <statement>
            <p>
                <m>x \in \mathbb{Q} \text{ iff } \exists p,q\in \mathbb{Z}\text{ with }q\neq0 \text{ such that }x=\frac{p}{q}\text{ and GCD}(p, q) =1 </m>
            </p>
            </statement>
        </definition>
    </p>
